<!--
  --- Question 59 ---
  This component represents the fifty-ninth question in the quiz.
-->

<div class="question-card" id="card-58" data-qid="58" data-type="single">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 59</span>
    <span class="q-tag single">Single Choice</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      What technique is used with UTP cable to help protect against signal interference from crosstalk?
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-58">
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">terminating the cable with special grounded connectors</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">twisting the wires together into pairs</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">wrapping a foil shield around the wire pairs</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">encasing the cables within a flexible plastic sheath</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn" id="submit-58" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-58">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-58"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        To help prevent the effects of crosstalk, UTP cable wires are twisted together into pairs. Twisting the wires together causes the magnetic fields of each wire to cancel each other out.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pagination-controls">
      <button class="nav-btn" id="prev-58">Previous</button>
      <span class="page-indicator">59 / 60</span>
      <button class="nav-btn" id="next-58">Next</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
